The paper deals with multimodal sentiment analysis, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a gated mechanism for attention-based learning, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, since the paper deals with multiple modalities, including text, audio, and video, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category.
